Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.89,0:00:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always in your way.\NYou can see the trouble we're having with the body right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.32,0:00:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at all this.\NThis is all because of the body, understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.12,0:00:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of my mouth and your ears.\NYou see, if we didn't all have bodies here,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.52,0:00:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd just all be together in one big spiritual space,\Nand you would all know what I know, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.82,0:00:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we'd have one mind,\Nand we'd just all know what everybody else knows,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.17,0:00:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don't even have to verbalize\Nand go through all this whole talking-ness business,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which I do for the sake of the audience.\NBut it takes an espresso to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.54,0:01:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the healings that people have,\Nthe result is not the time for them to leave this earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.95,0:01:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're destined to leave at a certain time,\Nthen you can either leave in good condition
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.62,0:01:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or not such good condition.\NI told you about the old people in the nursing home,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.73,0:01:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, saying, help, help, help, help, help.\NYou know, and they got a stroke on this side
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.28,0:01:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and a stroke on this side,\Nand they're paralyzed with rheumatism all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.54,0:01:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Their kidneys are gone, their heart's gone.\NThey can't hear or see or smell anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.76,0:01:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're still going on.\NThey can't get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.65,0:01:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't get out of here.\NCan't get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.62,0:01:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when the time comes, you can't stay here.\NYou can't stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.62,0:01:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The door to the airplane opens up at 36,000 feet.\NOne person is withdrawn from that airplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.32,0:02:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, that was in the papers,\Nabout 10, 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.31,0:02:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was the stewardess.\ND.C., whatever it is, at 36,000 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.71,0:02:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The door suddenly blew open,\Nand exactly one person was extracted
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.78,0:02:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the 350 passengers.\NSo when karmically it's your time,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.75,0:02:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you ain't going to hang out.\NAnd if it isn't time, you can't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.43,0:02:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.25,0:02:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're conditioned at the time.\NYes, you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.66,0:02:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So the time of leaving is karmically set.\NBut you're conditioned,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.22,0:02:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other factors,\Nthey're up to personal choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is,\Nwhat will be helpful to keep in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.74,0:02:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,if one leaves a higher level of consciousness\Nand moves to a lower level of consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.43,0:02:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You change your expectations.\NYou change your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.19,0:02:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like somebody only went to fifth grade.\NRight away, your expectation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you shift your intellectual presentation to them\Nso they can comprehend it out of compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.62,0:03:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of compassion for somebody\Nwho's struggling,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,with the barest minimum of existence,\NI modify how I present a concept to them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.46,0:03:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it is mutually, meets mutual needs,\Nnot just my needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.65,0:03:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we like to tell everybody\Nhow democracy is so wonderful and this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.71,0:03:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's meaningful to somebody in the 400s.\NThat's meaningful to somebody in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.69,0:03:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To somebody who doesn't know where dinner is going\Nto come from tonight, it's so much palaver, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've been in places, you know.\NI'm thinking about South America on the coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.93,0:03:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not very left-brained right now.\NI can't tell you the name of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.12,0:03:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ikenema Beach, or what is that?\NWhat country is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.15,0:03:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Brazil.\NBrazil, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.62,0:03:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,On the side of the mountains there,\Nthe favelas where the peasants live.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.71,0:04:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how they live.\NA whole family of 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.83,0:04:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where they live.\NThere's a piece of tin here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.68,0:04:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's some string.\NThere's some paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.55,0:04:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some paper there.\NOver here, it looks like some used toilet paper, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.37,0:04:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind that is a piece of cardboard.\NBehind that is a couple of bricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.68,0:04:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind that is some stones.\NTen people live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.72,0:04:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I give you a lecture on democracy?\NYou stated that you had been to hell, and you felt this terror,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.27,0:04:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but you never saw an entity.\NSo what created terror?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.57,0:04:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the Buddha and Jesus Christ recommended,\Nand Jesus and the Buddha both said,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.57,0:04:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,avoid that which makes you go weak with kinesiology.\NI said that because they said that the spirit, after it leaves the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.98,0:05:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,will pay the karmic consequences for your decisions and choices in this lifetime.\NConsequently, it wasn't like they were trying to create a fear of hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.29,0:05:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,although religions have done so.\NIn this particular lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.60,0:05:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the extreme, there's been great spiritual extremes.\NAs I say, at age three, there was a confrontation that only occurs at level 850.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.26,0:05:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It came out of many lifetimes as a Hinayana Buddhist,\Nin which I followed the pathway of negation with great dedication.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And to me, at that time, the ultimate reality was the void.\NAnd so, each lifetime, I would go out into the void, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.00,0:05:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If the void was real,\Nthe ultimate reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there would have been nobody to report such an event.\NIn any case, because it's not real, you can't stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.80,0:06:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the void is very, very impressive.\NIt's very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.81,0:06:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you constantly negate everything,\Nyou eventually go into a state of nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.85,0:06:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is so overwhelmingly impressive, you're sure,\Nthis is the ultimate goal of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.00,0:06:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what a terror is then?\NNo, no, no terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.48,0:06:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing there to be afraid.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.48,0:06:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there's no terror in that.\NBut I turned away from it in this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.48,0:06:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because already at age 12,\NI'd had the experience of the infinite oneness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the most memorable quality was\Nyou're melted by the,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.92,0:06:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by the divine love.\NYou don't think any words in that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.33,0:06:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but the love melts any,\Nso the mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.33,0:07:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it's melted out by divinity,\Nthe presence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.81,0:07:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then,\Nthe state was not recoverable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.00,0:07:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't talk about personal experience today,\Nbecause it did not seem relevant to the lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.00,0:07:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but later on,\Noh yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.11,0:07:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,well later on,\NI'll give you the sequence of events then,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.11,0:07:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so it makes some kind of sense.\NWell, walking through the,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.11,0:07:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very religious spiritually,\Nhigh Episcopal,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.11,0:07:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a boy acolyte,\Na boy soprano with a cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.11,0:07:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and extremely religious,\Nand scrupulous in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.32,0:07:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One day walking through the woods,\Nall of a sudden the world was silent and still,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,like an infinite presence.\NAnd all of a sudden out of nowhere came
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.16,0:07:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a non-verbal awareness,\Nand I saw the totality,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:08:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to describe this,\NI saw the totality of the suffering of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.16,0:08:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.\NIt was a massive,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.42,0:08:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,non-verbal,\Nmassive awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and I grasped the totality of the suffering of all of man\Nthroughout all of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.42,0:08:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all description.\NIn that instant I became a profound atheist,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.05,0:08:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,\Nany God that can allow that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.05,0:08:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or create that,\Nin the mind of the child,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.31,0:08:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,see,\Nespecially Christianity in the 1930s,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.31,0:08:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the idea was that God creates everything,\Nsee,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.30,0:08:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore all tortures,\Nsuffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,pain,\Nand sin is the product of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.37,0:08:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sophisticated,\NI didn't realize that all the suffering of man
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.37,0:08:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is the product of the ego,\Nnot of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.37,0:08:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,see.\NSo what I was looking at was the totality
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.37,0:08:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of the production of the ego over time,\Nwhich is the mass of suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.37,0:08:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond description.\NBut I held God responsible for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.87,0:09:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so I instantly became an atheist,\Nand I didn't realize I was looking at the product of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.87,0:09:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the product of divinity,\Nsee.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.87,0:09:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway,\NI became a very intense atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.87,0:09:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I then went to a Jesuit university\Nwhere I got straight A in theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.87,0:09:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The better to argue the stupidity of theology\Nand the idiocy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.87,0:09:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of Aristotle\Nand St. Thomas Aquinas,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.87,0:09:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera,\Nof primary cause
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.87,0:09:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that idiotic childish intellectualization,\Nwhich I blew out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.87,0:09:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was like an intense preoccupation\Nwith a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.33,0:09:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was an essential truth\Nthat was reachable,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.33,0:09:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was unable to reach it,\Nand thereby intense effort
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.33,0:09:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and meditation,\Net cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.59,0:09:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally went into a sense of despair\Nabout the inability to contact
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.77,0:10:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the core of truth of existence,\NI guess driven by the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.77,0:10:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that I experienced at age three,\Nbut I'd forgotten about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.77,0:10:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nin searching for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.77,0:10:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of an ultimate answer,\NI went into a profound state of actual hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.28,0:10:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I investigated all the levels of consciousness,\Nincluding the depths of hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.41,0:10:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and driven into hell,\Nas a Dante,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.87,0:10:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,how Dante knew the nature of hell,\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.87,0:10:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I never asked whether he'd been there,\Nbut it was absolutely accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.19,0:10:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As I went into it,\Nthe upper layers of hell
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.19,0:10:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do with chopping people up and torture\Nand sort of Saddam Hussein's son's kind of deviltry,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.19,0:10:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which are just jacks for openers,\Nchopping people up and torching them to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.19,0:10:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that's hell.\NThat isn't hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.19,0:10:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just the warning\Nthat you're getting close to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.19,0:10:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it really gets severe,\Nand then it gets agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.27,0:11:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the agony reaches beyond what you can bear,\Nit suddenly gets worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.27,0:11:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point,\Nthere's a knowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.27,0:11:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,almost like you see a sign that says,\Nabandon all hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.27,0:11:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,ye who enter here.\NI think Dante wrote those exact words,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw those words.\NAnd then you enter a level of hell
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond imagination.\NNobody's imagination can imagine it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.24,0:11:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of horrific despair,\Nand it's forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.72,0:11:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the highest levels of consciousness\Nare forever and beyond time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.72,0:11:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the lowest depths of hell are timeless.\NNow you are in the absolute hopeless despair
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.23,0:11:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with no hope ever of getting out of this state,\Nand you begin to realize what forever means.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.23,0:11:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever agony.\NForever despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.23,0:11:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the horror of where you're at hits you.\NAt that level of hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.32,0:12:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all description,\Nout of this consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.89,0:12:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the prayer arose.\NIf there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.89,0:12:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget I was a profound atheist at the time,\Nif there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.00,0:12:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask him to help me.\NAnd then there was oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.40,0:12:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometime later,\NI don't know whether it was hours or a day or what,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.87,0:12:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness returned,\Nand now it was a complete and total transformation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.87,0:12:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in which a personal self had dissolved.\NThere was only awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.38,0:12:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,being the totality and allness of the presence of God\Nas all existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.63,0:12:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The stunning beauty of it left one speechless.\NThe mind no longer existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.12,0:12:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The tail end of the mind disappeared into the silence.\NThe tail end of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.19,0:12:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,was struck dumb with awe.\NThe revelation of the splendor of the existence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.35,0:13:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as all existence and all of its stunning beauty\Nshone forth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.01,0:13:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and blew out whatever remained of the mind\Nand fried it out forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.01,0:13:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's never had the audacity\Nto think a thought since.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.01,0:13:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So what remains to speak then\Nis a presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.42,0:13:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which is silent.\NIf I listen to the mind now,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.59,0:13:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it says nothing.\NIt's just an infinite silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.59,0:13:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But the intentionality of expression\Ncoming out of your question,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.59,0:13:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance,\Nthe answering this is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.59,0:13:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own spontaneously,\Nand I myself have nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.27,0:13:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry you asked.\NThat's some heavy stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Two quick questions.\NDr. Hawkins, I was wondering
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.39,0:13:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,if you and Werner Erhard\Nare familiar with each other's work?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.39,0:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NI'm familiar with Werner's work, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Werner Erhard.\NYes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.75,0:14:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people here have done this.\NHow many have done this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.75,0:14:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all the older people here have done this, yeah.\NThe younger ones are too young to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was great fun.\NEverybody did it back in the 70s, I think it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.69,0:14:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.\NIt's by a different name now, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.82,0:14:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I was also wondering if you knew of the work,\Nthe wisdom teachings of Avatar Adidas Samraj.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.82,0:14:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wondering if you knew of the wisdom teachings\Nof Avatar Adidas Samraj.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.26,0:14:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, okay.\NThere's a million gurus out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.46,0:14:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't calculate them all.\NI thought you said Ramana Maharshi at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.07,0:14:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I mean...\NThat was one of his...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.07,0:14:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That was one of his...\NNo, Ramana Maharshi and Asagadatta Maharaj
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.19,0:14:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,both calibrated in the low 700s.\N700 is the level of sage, sage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.19,0:14:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't usually change.\NThe sage usually goes in at 700,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.63,0:15:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,usually never leaves where they are,\Nand stays there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.99,0:15:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,See, consciousness tends to revolve of its own accord.\NIn other words, you can go into bliss state
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's absolutely perfect.\NThere's no necessity to go any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.72,0:15:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And consciousness may or may not stay there.\NAs I said, 50% of the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.97,0:15:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the person just leaves the body.\NExtremely rarely, extremely rarely,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.97,0:15:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely, extremely rarely,\Nonly a few in every generation or century even,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.10,0:15:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,does consciousness then start moving\Nfrom like 700 to 800 to 900 to 1000.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.10,0:15:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And it does it of its own accord,\Nunasked,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.20,0:15:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no one there to ask it to move ahead.\NThere's no incompleteness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.51,0:15:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason when you're sitting there\Nin a state of complete and total bliss
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.51,0:15:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and the infinite holiness of the presence\Nto suspect that consciousness could move
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.37,0:15:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere than where it is\Nbecause it's complete and total from moment to moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.37,0:16:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing I forgot to explain about\Nhow one experiences reality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.27,0:16:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the Newtonian paradigm,\Neverything is always incomplete
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.52,0:16:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and moving to completeness.\NOnce you let go of that paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.90,0:16:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you stop projecting that onto phenomena,\Nyou see that because all is,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.90,0:16:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all represents creation, continuous creation,\Nwhat you now see is everything goes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.90,0:16:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from completeness to completeness to completeness,\Nfrom perfection to perfection to perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.90,0:16:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not go from imperfection to perfection.\NThe half-unfolded rose is absolutely
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.45,0:16:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and perfectly and completely a half-unfolded rose.\NIt's perfect now, it's perfect now,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.45,0:16:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's perfect now, it's perfect now,\Nit's perfect now, it's perfect now,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.45,0:16:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's perfect now, it's complete now,\Nit's perfect now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.76,0:17:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NHow it transforms, how you experience the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.40,0:17:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that everything is perfection\Nevery instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.64,0:17:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that's going on in this room\Nis absolutely perfect right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.78,0:17:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,None of it should be or could be\Nor is doing anything other than
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.78,0:17:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,what is at this moment.\NAnd that's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.81,0:17:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We go from perfection to perfection,\Nfrom completion to completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.81,0:17:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we witness that way, creation,\Nand realize that it's divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.13,0:17:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're witnessing divinity\Nand the unfolding of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.13,0:17:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to thank you\Nfor your contribution to humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.07,0:18:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate it.\NOh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.13,0:18:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Pepsi.\NI have the problem of abundance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.13,0:18:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there's all these workshops on abundance.\NI do workshops on the problem of abundance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.13,0:18:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you do with abundance?\NHow can you drink three Pepsis at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.13,0:18:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NThis is just representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.39,0:18:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you let go\Nof the sense of incompleteness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.39,0:18:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and see everything is complete,\Nyou realize that you are complete
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.39,0:18:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and total every instant.\NAnd you have no further needs or desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.50,0:18:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you want.\NSomebody says,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.50,0:18:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?\NI tell them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.50,0:18:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI have to make up something
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.50,0:18:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to make them happy.\NI need a new bow tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.50,0:18:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good.\NNow they're happy they have something
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.50,0:18:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can get you.\NBut, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.50,0:18:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,actually I have no need for a bow tie.\NI've got drawers full of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.50,0:18:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got drawers full of bow ties.\NI've got the world's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.50,0:19:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest collection of bow ties.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.50,0:19:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everything,\Nonce you see it correctly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,every moment you have all\Nthat you need at that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.50,0:19:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NAnd if you don't have anything to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have all that you need\Nin order to starve to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.30,0:19:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hard one to see.\NBut,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.30,0:19:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're meant to starve to death,\Nthen what you need
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.65,0:19:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is the absence of food\Nand you're provided with that need
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.65,0:19:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,by the absence of food.\NAnd so you can happily starve to death
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.65,0:19:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,full of self-pity,\Nresentment,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and remorse.\NAnd hate God
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.65,0:20:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and now feel vindicated in hating him.\NWith what you just said in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.79,0:20:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't need any answers to anything\Nand if you'd sign this book,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.79,0:20:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be great.\NAnd I'll give you a dollar, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.11,0:20:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Your desires are already fulfilled.\NThat's a divine dollar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.11,0:20:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mark this one.\NThis one is special.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.11,0:20:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll never spend this one.\NYou wrote special on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.11,0:20:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a holy dollar.\NA holy dollar, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.50,0:20:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I really don't have a question either.\NI'd just like to thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask you to sign my book.\NI would be happy to sign it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.80,0:20:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's a gift to me\Nto allow me to sign your book.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.60,0:20:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I might use this dollar to save my life\Non the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.44,0:20:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like you to sign my book.\NBut I also have a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.44,0:20:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The Middle East calibrates now\Nbelow the 200 level.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.44,0:21:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any theories or ideas\Naround how long it's going to take
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.44,0:21:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or what could be the catalyst\Nto get them above 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.44,0:21:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't explain that fully.\NWe really didn't get in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the shortage of time\Nhow to transcend the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.35,0:21:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the ego is a substitute for God.\NYeah, we explained in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.40,0:21:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Egocentricity is,\Nit seeks to displace God as the authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.00,0:21:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, The Course in Miracles explains that very well.\NAnd that's the reason I like the Course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.02,0:21:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it really explains the authority problem.\NBut,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.08,0:21:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what was your question?\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.16,0:21:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, the ego then feeds off of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.16,0:21:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is devoid of divine energizing,\Nit's self-energizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.16,0:21:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ego survives,\Nthis is something important
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.16,0:21:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have said this morning,\Nby the juice it gets out of its positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.16,0:22:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets so much juice out of hatred.\NWhy should it give up hatred?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.16,0:22:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch the two sides on the newsreel every night\Nshooting at each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.50,0:22:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,throwing bricks at each other over the barricades.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.50,0:22:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Throwing rocks,\Nshooting at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.03,0:22:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in a state of high joy.\NThere's no higher joy than throwing rocks at the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.20,0:22:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can then provoke the police\Nto finally let go of the dogs or shoot somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.28,0:22:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you can get on television with the victim.\NThis justifies shooting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.28,0:22:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NSo, the payoff on this is tremendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.28,0:22:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And the leaders of those countries\Nmaintain their political position
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.99,0:22:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,based on playing this game endlessly.\NYou know that they've been at it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.01,0:22:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,since I've been on the planet?\NThey've been at it since I've been on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.33,0:22:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Same boundaries, same people,\Nsame justification, same ideology,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.33,0:23:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,same motivation, same payoff.\NSo, it's going to go on to perpetuity?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.33,0:23:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It could go on another thousand years.\NBecause the ego will juice everything out of injustice,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.47,0:23:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,remorse, revenge,\Nhatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.50,0:23:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The spleen is a very strong chakra in those regions.\NSo, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.50,0:23:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,those are regions that live in the chakra of the spleen.\NHatred, envy, jealousy, untruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.93,0:23:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How long can they live there?\NThousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.07,0:23:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, ma'am.\NJust do nothing but signing books
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.14,0:23:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,after we get a few more questions.\NIs that what we should do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.03,0:23:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NAll right, but the questions can go on,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.03,0:23:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll just have people sign books real fast\Nso we can sign a lot of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.03,0:23:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can still talk to me\Nand I'll be happy to hug you all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.03,0:23:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and answer as many questions as I can.\NMy ambition is to hug everybody who's here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.03,0:24:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I'll make it or not.\NWell, I was going to ask for a handshake,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.74,0:24:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'll take the hug.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.76,0:24:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's my question.\NOkay, so at the instant we're born,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.50,0:24:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we come in with a certain level of consciousness\Nand we come in with a predetermined time of our death,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.50,0:24:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so we might as well not think about it.\NIt's just going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.50,0:24:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, then for want of another word,\Nwe come in with this soul that has karmic potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.50,0:24:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd you said the soul or this karmic potential
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.50,0:24:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is influenced by conditions\Nof the field of infamy, of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.50,0:24:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of whatever term you want.\NI guess my question to you is,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.50,0:25:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in this karmic soul,\Ncan I have any influence on that field
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.21,0:25:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and is my influence based on will and choice?\NI don't think you phrased it exactly correctly,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.26,0:25:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but you won't influence the field.\NBut in other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.29,0:25:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I picture this life as purgatorial.\NIn other words, we have a huge range of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.29,0:25:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Huge range of choice at every instant.\NThen we have our karmic potential
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.80,0:25:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have our karmic obligations.\NWe're already born with a certain IQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.03,0:25:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're born with a certain kind of body.\NYou're an endomorph, mesomorph, or ectomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.03,0:25:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're born with a certain IQ.\NSome people are born genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.03,0:25:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are born not so bright.\NSome people are born strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.44,0:25:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are born weak.\NSome are born rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.50,0:25:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are born poor, see?\NSo now, starting out,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.85,0:25:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you find yourself again in a physical body\Nin a human lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.61,0:26:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The choices that are karmically destined to come up\Nwill come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.61,0:26:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And this time you have a choice to answer differently.\NThis time you have a choice to answer differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.09,0:26:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All the choices, all my choices,\Nare karmic choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.09,0:26:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't exist without choice,\Nso everything that I choose
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.09,0:26:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything I think is a karmic choice.\NIs that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.64,0:26:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very,\Nthere's various levels to this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.64,0:26:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain patterns which are inherent\Nwithin the energy field of the spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.21,0:26:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as it reincarnates.\NSome of these karmic patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.92,0:26:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to be of greater importance\Nor greater pressure than others.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.92,0:26:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are going to be trivial.\NSome are going to be surely optional.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.13,0:26:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you see, in a complex pattern,\Na small choice made here
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.57,0:27:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,will put you in a different realm.\NWhere other karmic propensities are going to come up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.57,0:27:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,where if you don't make that choice, it won't come up.\NSo you see an endless series
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.74,0:27:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,like a mosaic.\NIf I say yes to that, that puts me over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.76,0:27:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here I have these options.\NIf I say no to that, it puts me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.76,0:27:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here I don't have those options.\NSo from moment to moment
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.76,0:27:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I am constantly determining my own karmic destiny.\NUnderstand that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.76,0:27:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say yes to that,\NI now have the option to say yes to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.76,0:27:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say no to that,\NI can't say...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.76,0:27:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say no, I won't go to Europe.\NI don't have the option of walking the maze
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.76,0:27:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in Chartres Cathedral.\NIf I'm there, is it a maze?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.76,0:27:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is.\NIt's an amazing place, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.76,0:27:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If I get there and I say,\NI think I'll walk it while I'm there,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.76,0:27:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I get there, there's chairs all over it.\NObviously, the church authorities don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.76,0:27:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,trails of people going out down the street\Nwalking the maze, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.76,0:28:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the complex or whatever it is.\NSo every choice then alters your options
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.76,0:28:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,from moment to moment.\NAnd you see the endlessness and the complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.76,0:28:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of the energy field of consciousness.\NBut here's then the last point.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.96,0:28:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That being the case,\Nwhat's the difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.96,0:28:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly weaving your way through\Nall the choices
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.96,0:28:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and the concept of surrender?\NBecause one choice you have is to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.43,0:28:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is a choice that's present all the time.\NSo when I'm experiencing pain,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.49,0:28:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I can surrender the experience to God\Nor I can resist it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.49,0:28:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If I resist it, that intensifies the pain.\NThe way to disappear a thing is to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.49,0:28:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,let go resisting it.\NAll experiencing comes out of resisting.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.44,0:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the persistence of the ego\Nthat you experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:29:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember on that chart up there we put\Nthere's the witnesser, the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.53,0:29:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing experiencing what's going on here.\NWithin this entity whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.78,0:29:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to experience it.\NWhat would it experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.26,0:29:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's conscious and aware,\Nbut it's not experiencing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.85,0:29:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bugger.\NAll you can see is getting your way through
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.74,0:29:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole endless complexity of choices.\NAnd every choice determines your options.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.23,0:29:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, if I say yes to this,\Nthat opens these options.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.23,0:29:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a mouse cannot decide\Nto become a gopher.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.39,0:29:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's karmically already bound to certain choices.\NSo you as a human being
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.39,0:29:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,inherit a body and a brain\Nand your own karmic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.39,0:30:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So your choices are not unlimited.\NYou cannot decide to become
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.92,0:30:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a champion wrestler right now.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.59,0:30:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't.\NI guess then, I guess then,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.59,0:30:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this is pretty heavy,\Nbut ideally, faith is realizing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.11,0:30:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you were to live only in the moment,\Nevery single moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.11,0:30:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and every single moment you were to surrender,\Nthat's as close as you're going to come
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.63,0:30:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to enlightenment in this body.\NThere's nothing to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.96,0:30:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one has surrendered too.\NThat's all an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.96,0:30:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the fact that you need to become enlightened\Nis already a great illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.21,0:30:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you have to forgive me.\NI get very nervous in front of crowds
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.21,0:30:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm like, okay,\Na newborn baby to all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.21,0:31:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you become more nervous,\Nyou're not nervous enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.21,0:31:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll try.\NIf you were really nervous,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.30,0:31:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be complaining about it.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.30,0:31:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, all right.\NNow, my question is,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.47,0:31:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the greatest lie of our time\Nright now that we have to be careful of,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.47,0:31:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Southern Baptist convert to Catholic,\Nso the fear of hell is ingrained, kind of.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.55,0:31:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyhow, is that there is no hell.\NDon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.55,0:31:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,God is all loving.\NGod is all forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.55,0:31:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had to narrow my faith down\Nto where it was something I could live with.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.55,0:31:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I finally came up with\Nwas the face in front of my face
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.55,0:31:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and intent is everything.\NI mean, actions, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.92,0:31:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what you always heard,\Nactions can't get me anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.92,0:31:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But what is it?\NI mean, your description of hell
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.45,0:32:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,scared me to death.\NI'm back to the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.45,0:32:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt isn't like it's a realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.34,0:32:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it's a level of consciousness.\NYou see, you're still within
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.44,0:32:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the realm of consciousness.\NTo abandon God, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.75,0:32:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is to throw yourself at the mercy\Nof word consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.92,0:32:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are regions of consciousness\Nthat you really don't want to experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.36,0:32:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NWhat was it you said?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.60,0:32:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I mean, you described hell.\NSo what you're really saying is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.60,0:32:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,hell most definitely exists.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.60,0:32:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's personalized.\NHell is personalized for each individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.60,0:32:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?\NIf they choose?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.60,0:32:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If they choose it?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.19,0:32:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But hell does exist.\NAnd experientially,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.27,0:32:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,both heaven and hell are experiential.\NThey're purely subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.27,0:33:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NIt's only subjectivity that even,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.75,0:33:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,could even say they exist.\NYou say they exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.92,0:33:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told you the experience.\NYeah, the experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.92,0:33:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThe experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.92,0:33:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ, you know, said that.\NBuddha said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.11,0:33:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And everyone can just sit back and relax.\NLean into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.68,0:33:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor tells me this\Ncounts out about seven, seven-fifty, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.11,0:41:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NOh, that's what the whole lecture's about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.63,0:41:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be willing to surrender the juice\Nthat you get out of the ego's positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.63,0:42:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be willing to surrender the juice of self-pity,\Nthe juice of resentment,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.63,0:42:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the juice of hatred,\Nthe juice of getting even.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.63,0:42:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All the negative payoffs.\NYou're willing to surrender the negative payoffs to the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.73,0:42:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you dissolve it.\NSounds simple enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.01,0:42:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NWe didn't get into that in the lecture today.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.01,0:42:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Doc, thanks for all the help.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.71,0:42:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you sign a book and get a picture, maybe?\NYou bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.98,0:42:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Doc, how did you lose that thumb?\NWell, karmically, there's a story behind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.98,0:42:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually I did it with a circular saw.\NIt kicked back.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.17,0:42:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so fast.\NYou always say, well, it's off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.17,0:43:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I couldn't get my hand out of the way in time.\NIf it starts to kick back, you don't have enough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.17,0:43:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It moves faster than the speed of light.\NIt's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.78,0:43:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't get a chance to make a decision.\NSo you got more books in your works?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.78,0:43:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have one major book, yeah,\NI've been working on it for a year or two already.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.78,0:43:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to keep writing, though?\NYeah, this one's going to take another year anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.07,0:43:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be a major buster.\NThanks a bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.11,0:43:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, September 3.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.01,0:43:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.28,0:43:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful the field brought me to you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.28,0:43:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Many, many things.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.36,0:43:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's supposed to be short.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.36,0:43:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one's an angel.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.36,0:43:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So patient.\NShe's my angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.36,0:44:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God for her.\NHey, there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.32,0:44:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is subjectivity.\NWe didn't get into that too heavily today, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.05,0:44:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So are you going to have a cigarette later?\NWe're going to, yeah, if you're still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.73,0:44:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be great.\NI didn't want to get distracted.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.73,0:44:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, here we go.\NWe have a ritual smoke together.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.73,0:44:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah?\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.73,0:44:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tribal custom.\NEverything's holy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.73,0:44:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt's a Native American custom.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.53,0:44:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, David.\NNice to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.53,0:44:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been reading your book.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.53,0:44:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep reading.\NGood, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.53,0:44:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep up the good work.\NI have many questions, but there's too many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.53,0:44:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NHas been a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.53,0:44:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.53,0:44:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.53,0:44:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.53,0:44:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.36,0:44:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a blessing to hear you.\NYeah, I'm glad you enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.36,0:44:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I have questions, too, but I'll come back sometime.\NIf they ask easy ones, we can answer them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.36,0:44:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIf they ask easy ones, but they ask these hard ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.36,0:44:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They think of such complicated questions.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.36,0:45:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything that I would have asked had already been answered.\NAre we going to calibrate the audience before and after?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.42,0:45:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.42,0:45:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOkay, this audience at the end of the lecture was over 440, 444, 445.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.42,0:45:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,10 points.\NThey went up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.42,0:45:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,444.\N444.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.42,0:45:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,444.\N444.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.42,0:45:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,444.\N444.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.32,0:45:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,444.\N444.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.32,0:45:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,444.\N444.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.32,0:45:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,444.\N444.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.32,0:45:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,444.\N445.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.32,0:45:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,445.\N10 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.32,0:45:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They went up.\N435 to 445.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.86,0:45:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that an average calibration?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.86,0:45:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,An audience, 10 points.\NSome that are higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.86,0:45:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's some that are really low.\NSome really got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.86,0:45:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Some got it.\NSome got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.86,0:45:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Some got it this much lower.\NYeah, some people went down, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.86,0:45:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the smarter ones went up 20 points.\NOkay!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.86,0:45:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who are really listening did go up more than 10 points, but the average is 10\Npoints, which is pretty good for a whole bunch of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.86,0:45:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.86,0:45:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.86,0:45:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.86,0:45:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, ma'am.\NThank you, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.86,0:45:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, ma'am.\Nfor a whole field.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.30,0:45:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?\NIs he leaving right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.21,0:46:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're leaving right away?\NRalph, did you come down by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.15,0:46:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he brought a friend.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.59,0:46:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He brought a friend.\NOh, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.15,0:46:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're looking good, Ralph.\NYou're looking better.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.42,0:46:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYour head is shinier.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.38,0:46:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows you're getting better.\NI thought it was the reason you were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.36,0:46:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I was a reflective mirror.\NNo, you do look better.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.36,0:46:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You look better, you know.\NYeah, it's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.01,0:46:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does one do when they're by themselves\Nfor the questions and the testing?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.44,0:46:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I would use this system.\NI mean, you find somebody to work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.86,0:46:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You find somebody to work with.\NAnd certain people work really well
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.07,0:46:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and easy together.\NAnd other people don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.96,0:46:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So find somebody you just sort of work easy with, you know?\NAnd it sort of just automatically happens
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.25,0:47:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when you find the right person.\NThank you for your contributions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.55,0:47:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get your flowers?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.17,0:47:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for asking me.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.67,0:47:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet.\NYeah, we sent you flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.17,0:47:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We might have been out too.\NWe were.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.11,0:47:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We were.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.48,0:47:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.32,0:47:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.\NYeah, you bet. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.55,0:47:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking me.\NI love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.17,0:47:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I finished this book last night\Nwhen my dad died.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.40,0:47:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd it helped me to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.00,0:47:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,how much more joyous I am\Nthan I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.13,0:47:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm very grateful.\NOh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.42,0:47:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not.\NNo, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.51,0:47:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat's really good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.42,0:47:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NYeah, hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.05,0:47:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you a very quick question?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.98,0:47:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you talked about\Nthere was a set point
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.26,0:47:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for the time of our death, basically.\Nthat there's already a set time for our death.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.53,0:47:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What was your question?\NYour question is, is there also a set point
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.51,0:48:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for where we will be on the map of consciousness at that point?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.71,0:48:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So freedom of choice, power of intention, free will,\Nall that plays a part in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.57,0:48:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you come in with a calibrated level of consciousness.\NThat puts you somewhere in the field, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.40,0:48:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThen you've got your options.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.40,0:48:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when you leave the body,\Nyou're going to gravitate to that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.44,0:48:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person who has gravitated to hatred and hating God\Nwill automatically find himself in the realm of hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.80,0:48:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't condemn him there.\NThe one who chooses gentleness and love
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.80,0:48:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is automatically going to gravitate to people who are gentle and loving, you know?\NJust like some people...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.76,0:48:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt's for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.40,0:48:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people like, you know, the quiet, peaceful, rural.\NSo they automatically are going to move there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.09,0:48:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not going to hang out in New York City, see?\NOther people like the excitement of New York City
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.94,0:49:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the high of the solar plexus.\NSo they live in New York City.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.82,0:49:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you a question?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.13,0:49:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you've never alluded to this in any of your work,\Nbut did Jesus ever come to you and guide you in the right way?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.84,0:49:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What will?\NDid Jesus ever come to you and guide you in the right way?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.32,0:49:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo, she was afraid of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.38,0:49:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She was afraid of you.\NShe was afraid of the end of the line, and then she didn't have the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.01,0:49:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She was afraid of everybody here.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.50,0:49:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I just...\NSee, as a consciousness...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.76,0:49:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need some more drinks, water?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.59,0:49:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consciousness, a great consciousness,\Nthe consciousness of Jesus makes itself known all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.07,0:49:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and is always available.\NAll we have to do is ask for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.65,0:49:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is present right here at this moment in between the two of us.\NI need to ask you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.65,0:50:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't drink that.\NThe body of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.90,0:50:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a lot on the body of Jesus.\NThe body of Jesus is just an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.90,0:50:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The body of physicality means nothing.\NSomeone, like, could go to bed or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.90,0:50:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, look that up for me.\NThe reality of Christ is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.90,0:50:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness that supports our consciousness as we speak\Nis already present.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.59,0:50:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me, when I was a little girl,\Nhe came in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.53,0:50:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NHe came to me when I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.53,0:50:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He came to my room.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.53,0:50:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And he comes in my dreams.\NAnd he stands and he cries.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.53,0:50:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NIt takes literal form.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.53,0:50:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To help guide?\NTo help awaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.32,0:50:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's always there, why does he show up in form?\NAnd why do I feel closer when he does?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.73,0:50:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you feel closer when what?\NWhen he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.73,0:50:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do I feel like something profoundly is shifting inside of me\Nwhen he is in my dreams?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.73,0:50:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be a natural thing,\Nbecause of the inner consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.73,0:50:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.73,0:50:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.73,0:50:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.73,0:50:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.73,0:50:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.73,0:51:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wonderful thing, because of the enormous amount of\Nspiritual energy and devotion devoted to Jesus and to his image
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.53,0:51:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and to the whole concept of the Christ, yeah?\NAnymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.48,0:51:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I enjoyed it immensely.\NI'm a big fan of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.69,0:51:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.69,0:51:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read all of your work.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.67,0:51:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an honor to be here.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.84,0:51:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,September 03.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.05,0:51:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.40,0:52:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NDr. Hawkins, my God, there is no hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.44,0:52:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You know why? My God is only love and compassion.\NI do not believe in hell, because he loves me no matter what I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.17,0:52:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't condemn you to hell, but you can condemn yourself to hell.\NOh, I won't, because I'm too much in love with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.17,0:52:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To be in love with God, it means to be in love with love.\NIf you're in love with love, then you won't be going near hell at all.
